                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/2907753142"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "what is the point of this test? it asserts that an error is thrown, but the PR description claims to want to support -1\r\n\r\noh, the first call is strict=false and the 2nd one is strict=true. that is ... really unclear, and we aren't asserting anything for the first call...",
            "commit_id": "db5e3fe7de590d8d883f7e981090cf56c3b99cbd",
            "created_at": "2026-03-09T20:24:48Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -180,6 +180,18 @@ describe('API/extmarks', function()\n     })\n   end)\n \n+  it('end_col is -1', function()\n+    set_extmark(ns, marks[1], 0, 0, {\n+      end_col = -1,\n+      end_row = 0,\n+      strict = false,\n+    })\n+    eq(\n+      \"Invalid 'end_col': out of range\",\n+      pcall_err(set_extmark, ns, marks[2], 0, 0, { end_col = -1, end_row = 0, strict = true })",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38095#discussion_r2907753142",
